    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Psalms",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 30,
        "summary": "David sings praises and gives thanks to the Lord\u2014David pleads for mercy.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "I will extol thee, O Lord; for thou hast lifted me up, and hast not made my foes to rejoice over me.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "O Lord my God, I cried unto thee, and thou hast healed me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Heal.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "O Lord, thou hast brought up my soul from the grave: thou hast kept me alive, that I should not go down to the pit.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 86:13; Acts 2:34; D&C 132:39.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 16:10.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 36
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Sing unto the Lord, O ye saints of his, and give thanks at the remembrance of his holiness.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For his anger endureth but a moment; in his favour is life: weeping may endure for a night, but joy cometh in the morning.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Ps. 30:5 For his anger kindleth against the wicked; they repent, and in a moment it is turned away, and they are in his favor, and he giveth them life; therefore, weeping may\u00a0\u2026",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Joy.",
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 99
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 53
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 100,
                        "end": 106
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And in my prosperity I said, I shall never be moved.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Lord, by thy favour thou hast made my mountain to stand strong: thou didst hide thy face, and I was troubled.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 104:29; D&C 84:23 (21\u201323).",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 88
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 93
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "I cried to thee, O Lord; and unto the Lord I made supplication.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "What profit is there in my blood, when I go down to the pit? Shall the dust praise thee? shall it declare thy truth?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Ps. 30:9 When I go down to the pit, my blood shall return to the dust. I will praise thee; my soul shall declare thy truth; for what profit am I, if I do it not?",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 4
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0death.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 6:5.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 75
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 20
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Hear, O Lord, and have mercy upon me: Lord, be thou my helper.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Thou hast turned for me my mourning into dancing: thou hast put off my sackcloth, and girded me with gladness;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 31:13.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 61:3.",
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 109
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "To the end that my glory may sing praise to thee, and not be silent. O Lord my God, I will give thanks unto thee for ever.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
